The course covers the following subjects: fundamentals of investing, return and risk, analysis of bonds and stocks, long-term corporate financial planning, corporate financing and cost of capital, capital budgeting, corporate failure and bankruptcy. Some topics have to be covered by students independently (as out-of-class activities).
The course will consist of series of interactive lectures that assume active students participation. There will also be computer-based practical sessions. Students will have to complete a home group project and present this in a seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give in-depth overview of concepts and principles of corporate finance and analysis and management of investments that are largely applied in practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the successful completion of the course students have acquired knowledge about main concepts, theories and models in corporate finance and investments; students have become more familiar with an appropriate financial terminology. They also have acquired some proficiency in applying financial theories and methods in practice (e.g. how to conduct financial analysis of a company, how to estimate cost of capital, how to evaluate profitability of investment projects, how to analyze stocks and bonds, and evaluate securities' risk). Students also have advanced their skills in spreadsheet-based financial modeling (using MS Excel). Team-work and organizational skills shall be also developed by the end of the course.
